From political parties to civil society, social media is awash with tributes to the struggle icon, Ahmed Kathrada, who died early on Monday morning.  The anti-apartheid activist died after a short illness, and a memorial service has been arranged for Tuesday morning.  The African National Congress said his life was a lesson in humility, tolerance and resilience.  The Thabo Mbeki Foundation said that he was so committed to principle, he refused to be broken by harassment, torture or imprisonment. Opposition parties and MPs also paid tribute.    To Ntate #AhmedKathrada, your life was spent in the fight for our freedom. May your soul rest in revolutionary peace #RIP pic.twitter.com/CmaFBcxD5Y  Civil society also joined the chorus of tributes.  Share this slide: 